<article class="guide-container p-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto bg-white rounded shadow mt-6">
  <header>
    <h1 class="h2 italic mb-6">How to: Deploy a Rails App (with Render)</h1>
  </header>
  <section class="mb-6">
    <h2 class="h3 accent mb-2">1. Deploy on Render</h2>
    <p>
      Follow the official Render docs:<br>
      <a href="https://render.com/docs/deploy-rails-8" target="_blank" class="underline cursor accent">
        render.com/docs/deploy-rails-8
      </a>
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2">
      <li>
        <strong>Note:</strong> It's free, but your app will only run for a month.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <section class="mb-6">
    <h2 class="h3 accent mb-2">2. Other Deployment Options</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2">
      <li>
        <strong>Run your own server:</strong> You can deploy Rails on your own server. See the official deployment guide:<br>
        <a href="https://guides.rubyonrails.org/getting_started.html#deploying-to-production" target="_blank" class="underline cursor accent">
          guides.rubyonrails.org/getting_started.html#deploying-to-production
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Hack Club Nest:</strong> You can also deploy your app for free using <a href="https://hackclub.app/" target="_blank" class="underline cursor accent">Hack Club Nest</a>!! Make sure to join the Slack channel (#nest) if you do.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</article>